						<summary>

						<p>This is a verse in praise of a Pāṇḍya chief (<hi rend="italic">Kaṉṉi-vaḷanāḍaṉ</hi>) who defeated This chōla adversary in a battle and forced him to flee from the field with his legs seared (<hi rend="italic">Karikālaṉ</hi>). The writing is of about the 13th Century A.D.</p>						

